    What is the coldest month in Houston?
    January
    The climate of Houston is classified as a humid subtropical climate, with tropical influences. At an average temperature of 95 °F (35 °C), August is typically the warmest month of the year, whereas January is the coldest, at an average temperature of 63 °F (17 °C).

    Is Houston or Dallas hotter?
    Dallas and Houston are both located in Texas, but each city has a slightly different climate. Dallas has a humid subtropical climate, characterized by hot summers and mild winters. The city experiences less humidity than Houston, making summer temperatures feel more bearable.
